@startuml NormalAccountInsert_TaggingFlow
!theme plain
title Normal Account Insert - Tagging Flow (3 Steps)

start

:Input: GetNormalAccountEntity[];
note right
    Classified customers with:
    - CustId, CategoryId
    - ScanTaggingType
    - ScanTaggingTWType
    - ScanSpecialLicSubType
end note

:Create ProcessTaggingModel[];
note right
    Initialize tagging model:
    - TaggingID = 0
    - TaggingType = 0
    - TW metrics = 0
end note

partition "Step 1: Process TW Tagged Customers" {
  :Filter customers where ScanTaggingTWType = 1;
  
  if (Has TW customers?) then (yes)
    :CheckGroupBettingAndRejectCustomer;
    :Call CTS_NormalClassification_NormalAccount_TWGroupBettingAndReject_Check [SP];
    note right
        Returns TW Tagged customers:
        - TaggingID, TaggingType
        - TWBetCount
        - TWGroupBettingRate
        - TWTicketRejectRate
        - TWDesktopUsageRate
    end note
    
    :Create TWTaggedExcludeModel[];
    note right
        Join TW Tagged + CTS customers:
        - CustID
        - CategoryID
        - TaggingID
    end note
    
    :CheckTWTaggingExclude;
    :Call CTS_DC_NormalClassification_TW_CheckExclude [SP];
    note right
        Returns customers that SHOULD be tagged
        (Exclusion rules based on Category + Tagging)
    end note
    
    :Filter TW Tagged by exclusion result;
    note right
        Keep only customers returned by CheckExclude
    end note
    
    :Merge TW Tagged data to ProcessTaggingModel;
    note right
        If customer in TW Tagged result:
        - Set TaggingID
        - Set TaggingType
        - Set TW metrics
    end note
  else (no)
    :Skip TW tagging;
  endif
}

partition "Step 2: Process Association with PA" {
  :Filter customers where TaggingID = 0;
  note right
      Only process customers not
      already tagged in Step 1
  end note
  
  if (Has customers?) then (yes)
    :Join CustIds to comma-separated string;
    
    :GetCustsAssociationProblemAccount;
    :Call CTS_DC_CustClassification_GetTaggingByAssociationWithPA [SP];
    note right
        Returns customers associated with PA:
        - CustID
        - TaggingID (Association tagging)
        - TaggingType
    end note
    
    :Merge Association PA data to ProcessTaggingModel;
    note right
        If customer associated with PA:
        - Set TaggingID
        - Set TaggingType
    end note
  else (no)
    :Skip Association PA tagging;
  endif
}

partition "Step 3: Process TW Tagged Special LicSub" {
  :Filter customers where TaggingID = 0;
  note right
      Only process customers not
      tagged in Step 1 or Step 2
  end note
  
  if (Has customers?) then (yes)
    :Select CustID + ScanSpecialLicSubType;
    :Serialize to JSON;
    
    :GetTWTaggedCustBySpecialLicSub;
    :Call CTS_DC_NormalClassification_NormalAccount_TWTaggedSpecialLicSub_Check [SP];
    note right
        Returns Special LicSub TW Tagged:
        - CustID
        - TaggingID (Special LicSub tagging)
        - TaggingType
    end note
    
    :Merge TW Special LicSub data to ProcessTaggingModel;
    note right
        If customer has Special LicSub tagging:
        - Set TaggingID
        - Set TaggingType
    end note
  else (no)
    :Skip Special LicSub tagging;
  endif
}

:Convert ProcessTaggingModel[] to InsertNormalAccountEntity[];
note right
    Final result with:
    - CategoryId (from classification)
    - TaggingID (from 3-step tagging)
    - TaggingType
    - TW metrics (if TW tagged)
end note

:Output: InsertNormalAccountEntity[];

note right
  **Tagging Priority**:
  1. TW Tagged (Group Betting/Reject) - HIGHEST
  2. Association with PA - MEDIUM
  3. TW Tagged Special LicSub - LOWEST
  
  **Key Rules**:
  - Earlier tagging has priority
  - Later steps skip if already tagged (TaggingID != 0)
  - Exclusion rules apply to TW tagging
  - Association PA applied if not TW tagged
  - Special LicSub applied if no other tagging
end note

stop

@enduml

